[SN]TITLE[SN]
Boston Spa post office raid second suspect charged

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A second man has been charged with robbery following a raid at a West Yorkshire village post office.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mark Pick, 41, of Lea Farm Road, Leeds, is due to appear at Leeds Magistrates' Court charged with robbing the post office in High Street, Boston Spa.
He is also charged with possessing a firearm with intent to commit robbery.
A shotgun was fired and a staff member was struck with a crowbar during the raid on 23 March.
